channel.title: CVE Feed for Microsoft -- Windows 10 Version 1903 for 32-bit Systems
channel.description: The latest CVEs for Microsoft -- Windows 10 Version 1903 for 32-bit Systems

item.title: CVE-2020-0624|2024-08-04T06:11:04.656Z -- microsoft -- windows%2010%20version%201903%20for%2032-bit%20systems
item.description: An elevation of privilege vulnerability exists in Windows when the Win32k component fails to properly handle objects in memory, aka 'Win32k Elevation of Privilege Vulnerability'. This CVE ID is unique from CVE-2020-0642.

item.title: CVE-2020-0636|2024-08-04T06:11:04.575Z -- microsoft -- windows%2010%20version%201903%20for%2032-bit%20systems
item.description: An elevation of privilege vulnerability exists in the way that the Windows Subsystem for Linux handles files, aka 'Windows Subsystem for Linux Elevation of Privilege Vulnerability'.

item.title: CVE-2020-0796|2024-08-04T06:18:01.914Z -- microsoft -- windows%2010%20version%201903%20for%2032-bit%20systems
item.description: A remote code execution vulnerability exists in the way that the Microsoft Server Message Block 3.1.1 (SMBv3) protocol handles certain requests, aka 'Windows SMBv3 Client/Server Remote Code Execution Vulnerability'.
